Workflow for producing Tutorial

Uses Ubuntu package docbook-xsl 1.75.2+dfsg-3
Base dir doc/tutorial

1)
Create one Docbook file per language (filter stylesheet from http://docbooksml.sourceforge.net/)

xsltproc --stringparam language en --output tutorial_en.xml xsl/filter_language.xsl tutorial.xml
xsltproc --stringparam language fr --output tutorial_fr.xml xsl/filter_language.xsl tutorial.xml
xsltproc --stringparam language de --output tutorial_de.xml xsl/filter_language.xsl tutorial.xml

2)
Create html output assuming that gh-pages branch is checked.out into a folder MyExpenses.pages
parallel to the project root

xsltproc --stringparam base.dir ../../../MyExpenses.pages/tutorial/en/ xsl/tutorial.xsl tutorial_en.xml
xsltproc --stringparam base.dir ../../../MyExpenses.pages/tutorial/fr/ xsl/tutorial.xsl tutorial_fr.xml
xsltproc --stringparam base.dir ../../../MyExpenses.pages/tutorial/de/ xsl/tutorial.xsl tutorial_de.xml

now executed through ant target tutorial

3) Screenshots

I create screenshots with Eclipse DDMS from a virtual machine with Android-x86, 
with screenresolution set to 400x600.
The png should be stored into MyExpenses.pages/tutorial/{lang}/large.
The smaller image can be created with the following shell command
executed from MyExpenses.pages/tutorial and steps set to a list of numbers of changed
screenshots
steps="3 5 9"
for lang in en fr de
  do (
    cd ${lang}/large
    pwd
    for i in 3
      do
        convert step${i}.png -resize 50%  step${i}_klein.png
        pngnq step${i}_klein.png
        mv step${i}_klein-nq8.png ../step${i}.png
        rm step${i}_klein.png
      done
    )
  done
